{"id": "EUVD-2023-59708", "enisaUuid": "a66765db-feab-30f1-a2fd-8d04e5660cb7", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nthermal: core: call put_device() only after device_register() fails\n\nput_device() shouldn't be called before a prior call to\ndevice_register(). __thermal_cooling_device_register() doesn't follow\nthat properly and needs fixing. Also\nthermal_cooling_device_destroy_sysfs() is getting called unnecessarily\non few error paths.\n\nFix all this by placing the calls at the right place.\n\nBased on initial work done by Caleb Connolly.", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T18:31:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-30T18:31:04", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a7d736cc3c6cb0d7498bbfb56515d414e35e9510", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2846a7412f6246fd5171f51011bf76dfebcec0ee", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6c54b7bc8a31ce0f7cc7f8deef05067df414f1d8", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53012"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53012"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1c8b20d4-6e41-32d1-a539-3131093bc887", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c408b3d1d9bbc7de5fb0304fea424ef2539da616 <6c54b7bc8a31ce0f7cc7f8deef05067df414f1d8"}, {"id": "208c3442-0997-306b-b953-cf0d41250c16", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "108a6f91e2766a6d9142b1f2d90c07ac547eae7e <a7d736cc3c6cb0d7498bbfb56515d414e35e9510"}, {"id": "45521514-26f2-322a-864b-9f9348b755c5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4748f9687caaeefab8578285b97b2f30789fc4b4 <6c54b7bc8a31ce0f7cc7f8deef05067df414f1d8"}, {"id": "f097f474-b6ac-3707-9adc-03aa784c983c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "80bb3b901abe6560620505e5c734d140c4f73a07 <2846a7412f6246fd5171f51011bf76dfebcec0ee"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "5e681137-91cc-364c-afc8-314a4d9bf69b", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}